===Verb===
{{en-verb|splits|splitting|split}}

# {{transitive}} Of something solid, to divide fully or partly along a more or less straight line.
#:''He has '''split''' his lip.''
# {{transitive}} To [[share]]; to [[divide]].
#:''We '''split''' the money among three people''
# {{slang}} To [[leave]].
#:''Let's '''split''' this scene and see if we can find a real party.''
#  to [[separate]] or [[break up]].
#:''Did you hear Dick and Jane '''split'''?  They'll probably get a divorce.''

